 [ <a href="/weapons/individual/deepwater_harpoon.shtml?ID=830&page=1"> 1 </a> ] [ <a href="/weapons/individual/deepwater_harpoon.shtml?ID=830&page=2"> 2 </a> ] [ <a href="/weapons/individual/deepwater_harpoon.shtml?ID=830&page=3"> 3 </a> ] [ <a href="/weapons/individual/deepwater_harpoon.shtml?ID=830&page=4"> 4 </a> ]</center>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Keyne Falconer</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-10-20 15:53:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Personally...<BR>
<BR>
I want to get this item just to say I did it.  I also want to get my own dranned Ro armour, rather than buying it from others.<BR>
<BR>
What's the point of having quest weapons/armour if you don't actually do the quest?<BR>
<BR>
I have a lvl 21 Cleric and, with some help, I've completed the Boot, Gauntlet and Vambraces quests.  Next step is Greaves, then Bracers. (If the spawn time isn't bad, I'll get a friend to do the Bracer quest right after I do, then let her turn the items in when I do... four bars of enchanted Plat are going to be expensive though.)<BR>
<BR>
Back to this item.  Best options are: Plan on having three or four people.  One (or two) very high level to pull/kill the spectres.  One to follow Sentry Xyrin around with the potion (Some say the potion isn't required, I don't know for sure.  This person should be the Paladin who wants the weapon, btw.)  And the key to saving time... one person to hail Syn-something, the Sisterhood of Erollisi leader.  I believe the key phrase is "Where is Sentry Xyrin?"  But I could be wrong about the exact words.<BR>
<BR>
Last time I was in OOT, a pair of people were planning on going after this item...  As I didn't have a friend around to get rid of the spectres, I offered to triggered Xyrin for them.  First time, Xyrin spawned, they gave her the potion (faction bonus, non-measurable xp) and ran up the hill.  Specs were dead, so she stood around for awhile, then poofed... no Harpoon.  After a conference, it was decided that the PC Paladin needed to be nearby (preferably right next to Xyrin) when she poofed.  I triggered Xyrin again... Specs were dead, so she stood around for awhile.  Then a Spec spawned and attacked the hapless PC, who was medding rather than just standing (medding increases your aggro radius, if you didn't know)... who died before the Spec could be pulled off.  Xyrin poofed, and again, no Harpoon.  They gave up after that, and the Spec hunters logged as well, so I didn't get a chance to try out my theories.<BR>
<BR>
If anyone would like to help me do this quest on Xegony, send a tell to Keyne or Angelsyn (my cleric)  I'm usually on most week-days from 6pm-1am PST.</font></td></tr></table>
